'''Agent ZNT-8''' was the lone [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] operative who remained at the [[Dankayo Base|Alliance base]] on [[Dankayo/Legends|Dankayo]] as an observer after its [[Battle of Dankayo|evacuation]]. Agent ZNT-8 survived the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy's]] [[Orbital bombardment/Legends|orbital bombardment]] by taking refuge in a deep-planet survival shelter, and emerged to find that the [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] attack had destroyed the base's [[Power generator/Legends|power generators]], preventing the complete self-destruction of the base computers. [[Stormtrooper/Legends|Stormtroopers]] from the [[Imperial Armored Transport]] [[Elusive (transport)|''Elusive'']] were sifting the ruins of the base, and had in fact recovered several datapacks full of sensitive intelligence. Agent ZNT-8 was armed with a couple of [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonators]] and some [[Detonite/Legends|detonite]], and his last log entry recorded his intention to attack the Imperials. The agent apparently failed their mission, inasmuch as the datapacks were evacuated on the ''Elusive'', bound for [[Coronar]], but they were able to alert the Alliance to the situation, and thanks to Agent ZNT-8's warning, another group of Alliance agents eventually intercepted and destroyed the shipment.

